        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. NATO defence systems shoot down Iranian ballistic missile over Turkey Middle East Issued on: 14/03/2026 - 13:37 Turkey's defence ministry says a ballistic missile fired from Iran and heading into Turkish airspace after passing Syria and Iraq was destroyed by NATO air and missile defence systems in the eastern Mediterranean Sea. It's the third such incident since the war began. Turkey's president Erdogan says his priority is to keep his country out of the war in the Middle East. Details by Morgan Ayre. Two weeks into the war in the Middle East, what is to expect? 14/03/2026 Analysis Middle East US deploys USS Tripoli amphibious assault ship to Middle East 14/03/2026 Middle East US military bombs military sites on Kharg island, Iranian media reports no damage 14/03/2026 Middle East War in the Middle East: A sailor stranded in the Gulf fears for his safety 13/03/2026 Middle East As 800,000 flee, half of Lebanon lives in war zones without markets, supplies or healthcare 13/03/2026 Middle East Lebanon’s Mission Impossible: Could US and Israeli pressure to disarm Hezbollah lead to civil war? 13/03/2026 Middle East Strait of Hormuz: Iran leverages control of a critical chokepoint in the global oil trade 13/03/2026 Middle East 'Mental, subjective impact': Iran taking on 'American might' with cyberterrorism 13/03/2026 Middle East Israel widens Lebanon bombing campaign to target north and central Beirut 13/03/2026 On the ground Middle East"
